In a country where economic instability is as common as coconuts, Brazilians appear to favor the stablecoin tether as their cryptocurrency of choice.<br data-v-f87c67ca="">
<br data-v-f87c67ca="">
The federal tax authority, which compiles data from foreign and local exchanges on cryptocurrency usage, said that the value of all transactions for tether jumped 58% last year compared to a year earlier. Bitcoin and ether, also widely used, saw decreases of more than 60% from 2021.&nbsp;
